# GalaxyCo Standards (Monorepo)
- TypeScript strict; avoid 'any' unless justified.
- Validate external input with Zod.
- apps/web: Next.js App Router; Server Components by default; Server Actions for mutations.
- Styling: Tailwind + shadcn/ui; keep design system consistent.
- Tests: Vitest; test behavior, not implementation.
- Monorepo: run via turbo; shared code in packages/*.
- Pre-commit: code must format & lint; no stray console.log (warn-only allowed during dev).

## GitKraken CLI Integration
- Use `gk ai commit --add-description` for AI-generated Conventional Commits
- Use `gk work start "<feature>"` to create feature branches with work item tracking
- Use `gk work pr create` for AI-generated PR descriptions
- Commit scopes: api, web, db, infra, scope-agent, call-agent, email-agent, note-agent, task-agent, roadmap-agent, content-agent

## MCP Server
- GitKraken MCP server installed for Cursor
- Provides git operations, GitHub API, and AI tools
- See docs/devtools/gitkraken-cli.md for details

